'''Jeong Yol''' ({{lang|ko|정욜}}; born October 19, 1978) is a [[South Korea]]n [[LGBT]] rights activist. Since the foundation of [[Solidarity for LGBT Human Rights of Korea]] in 1997, he has been an early member of SLRK. From 1998 to 2012, he had been a representative of SLRK. His real name is '''Jeong Min-suk''' (정민석).

During the college time, he acknowledged that himself was [[gay]]. Later, while serving his [[conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]], he came out as a homosexual. Then, his commanding officer took him to a mental hospital.<ref name="phito">[http://www.ohmynews.com/nws_web/view/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0000238084 동성애자 인권운동가 정욜씨의 삶] 오마이뉴스 2005.02.18 {{ko}}</ref> After his discharge, he worked as a pastry chef for six years.<ref>[http://www.catholicnews.co.kr/news/quickViewArticleView.html?idxno=8503 무지개 깃발 휘날리며, 성소수자로 연대하다] {{ko}}</ref>

In 1997, he joined SLRK. In 2000, he spent more time primarily for SLRK, From 2002 to 2012, he has been a representative of SLRK. In February 2003, the word "homosexual" was pointed as harmful word for youth by [[South Korea]]n government. So he struggled against the government with [[Kwak Yi-kyong]], [[Chang Pyong-kwon]] and others. In April 2004, banning of word "homosexual" for youth was eliminated in South Korea.

In 2003, he led a movement for the Elimination of Discrimination against LGBT. In 2004, he joined anti-war and peace movements.<ref>[http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=047&aid=0000026043 어리석은 자들의 진보적 인권운동 10년] {{ko}}</ref> Since 2006, he has fought for [[people living with HIV]]'s rights.<ref name="bisope">[http://www.ohmynews.com/NWS_Web/View/at_pg.aspx?CNTN_CD=A0000167087 <한겨레> '에이즈 기사' 규탄 기자회견 열려] 오마이뉴스 2004.02.04 {{ko}}</ref>

