'''Michael Kagan''' is an American academic and immigrant rights lawyer.  He is Professor of Law at the [[University of Nevada, Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.law.unlv.edu/faculty/michael-kagan.html|title=University of Nevada Las Vegas, William S. Boyd School of Law}}</ref> He is Director of the [https://law.unlv.edu/clinics/immigration UNLV Immigration Clinic], which specializes in deportation defense, including of unaccompanied children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thenevadaindependent.com/article/children-in-limbo-in-the-midst-of-immigration-enforcement-debate|title=Children in limbo in the midst of immigration enforcement debate|access-date=2017-08-18|language=en}}</ref>

Kagan played a leading role in the establishment of refugee legal aid programs that assist asylum-seekers applying for refugee status determination through the [[UN refugee agency]].<ref>[[Zachary D. Kaufman]] (2012). Social Entrepreneurship in the Age of Atrocities. Edward Elgar Publishing. pp. 42–43. {{ISBN|1781002215}}.</ref> He helped to found or develop Africa Middle East Refugee Assistance (AMERA) in [[Egypt]], and [http://asylumaccess.org Asylum Access], which is based in the United States. He also became a leading campaigner for reforms in the way the UN conducts refugee status determination, and started the website RSDWatch.org.<ref>[[Zachary D. Kaufman]] (2012). Social Entrepreneurship in the Age of Atrocities. Edward Elgar Publishing. pp. 42–43. {{ISBN|1781002134}}.</ref> 
Kagan completed his law degree at the [[University of Michigan]].

