{{Infobox political youth organization | name= Young European Movement UK | native_name= | colorcode= | logo= | caption= | logo2= | caption2= | leader = | deputy leader = | president = Juuso Järviniemi | vice president = James Evered, Chris Stenseth | executive vice president = | associate vice president = | membership director = | political affairs director = | communications director = Eoin Burgin | programs director = | development director = | national council chair = | national council vice-chair = | national council secretary = | chairperson = | chairman = | 1st vicechairman = | 2nd vicechairman = | co-chairperson = | co-chairman = | vice-chairperson = | vice-chairman = | national chairman = | national co-chairman = | secretary2 = | secretary general= | treasurer = Lisa Bruining | regional vice-chair = | executive director = | political director = | finance director = | website director = | spokesperson = | field director = | honorary chair = | founded= 1972 | merger of= | split from= | preceded by= | dissolved = | merged into= | succeeded by= | headquarters = [[United Kingdom]] | membership = 420 | ideology = | colours = | mother party= | state party= | international= | regional1_type= | regional1_name = | regional2_type= | regional2_name = | national = | newspaper = | magazine = | website = [http://yem.org.uk www.yem.org.uk] }} The '''Young European Movement UK''' (YEM UK) was formed in 1972 as a nonpartisan platform for under 35s to express their opinions on Europe. It is the UK branch of the [[Young European Federalists]] (JEF) and has a close relationship with the European Movement (EM) and other partners.
== Activities ==
YEM UK has organized and been present at various events such as marches and protests. In March 2017, an anti-[[Brexit]] protest was held in [[Edinburgh]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/thousands-of-brexit-protesters-pay-silent-tribute-to-westminster-attack-victims-1-8459323|title= Thousands of Brexit protesters pay silent tribute to Westminster attack victims|newspaper=Yorkshire Post|accessdate= 3 September 2017|date=25 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theneweuropean.co.uk/top-stories/anti-brexit-protesters-march-on-parliament-to-demand-a-voice-for-the-48-1-4948248|title= Anti-Brexit protesters march on parliament to demand a voice for the 48%|newspaper=The New European|accessdate= 3 September 2017|date=25 March 2017}}</ref>, at which the chairman of the local branch said: "We want to raise the issue in British and Scottish people's lives that you have lies in the referendum campaign that people were not held accountable for and, whether you voted Remain or Leave, that is a real issue."<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-edinburgh-east-fife-39394945|title= Crowds march in Edinburgh to support EU|newspaper=BBC News|accessdate= 3 September 2017|date=25 March 2017}}</ref>
